📊 2. Excel Files

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

🔹 What is an Excel File?

```text id="excel_def"
Excel files (.xlsx) store spreadsheet data in rows and columns with support for multiple worksheets.
```

---

📥 Install openpyxl

```bash id="install_openpyxl"
pip install openpyxl
```

---

📦 Import openpyxl

```python id="import_openpyxl"
from openpyxl import Workbook
from openpyxl import load_workbook
```

---

📄 Create Excel Workbook

---

💻 Example

```python id="create_workbook"
from openpyxl import Workbook

workbook = Workbook()

workbook.save(
    "students.xlsx"
)
```

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

✍️ Write Data to Excel

---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

💻 Example

```python id="write_excel"
from openpyxl import Workbook

workbook = Workbook()

sheet = workbook.active

sheet["A1"] = "Name"
sheet["B1"] = "Age"

sheet["A2"] = "Saakshi"
sheet["B2"] = 22

workbook.save(
    "students.xlsx"
)
```

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

📖 Read Excel File

------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

💻 Example

```python id="read_excel"
from openpyxl import load_workbook

workbook = load_workbook(
    "students.xlsx"
)

sheet = workbook.active

print(
    sheet["A2"].value
)

print(
    sheet["B2"].value
)
```

---

▶️ Output

```text id="excel_output"
Saakshi
22
```

---

🔄 Iterate Through Rows

---

💻 Example

```python id="iterate_rows"
from openpyxl import load_workbook

workbook = load_workbook(
    "students.xlsx"
)

sheet = workbook.active

for row in sheet.iter_rows(
    values_only=True
):
    print(row)
```

---

▶️ Output

```text id="iterate_output"
('Name', 'Age')
('Saakshi', 22)
```

------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

➕ Append New Row

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

💻 Example

```python id="append_row"
from openpyxl import load_workbook

workbook = load_workbook(
    "students.xlsx"
)

sheet = workbook.active

sheet.append(
    ["Alex", 21]
)

workbook.save(
    "students.xlsx"
)
```

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

📏 Get Maximum Rows & Columns

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

💻 Example

```python id="max_rows"
print(sheet.max_row)

print(sheet.max_column)
```

---

▶️ Output

```text id="max_output"
3
2
```

---

📄 Create Multiple Sheets

---

💻 Example

```python id="multiple_sheets"
from openpyxl import Workbook

workbook = Workbook()

workbook.create_sheet(
    "Employees"
)

workbook.create_sheet(
    "Sales"
)

workbook.save(
    "company.xlsx"
)
```

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

✏️ Update Cell Value

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

💻 Example

```python id="update_cell"
sheet["B2"] = 23

workbook.save(
    "students.xlsx"
)
```

---

❌ Delete Row

---

💻 Example

```python id="delete_row"
sheet.delete_rows(2)

workbook.save(
    "students.xlsx"
)
```

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

📊 CSV vs Excel

| Feature | CSV | Excel |
|----------|----------|----------|
| File Type | `.csv` | `.xlsx` |
| Multiple Sheets | ❌ | ✔ |
| Formatting | ❌ | ✔ |
| Charts | ❌ | ✔ |
| Speed | Faster | Slightly Slower |
| Storage | Plain Text | Binary/XML |

